  "local_port": 37272,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I custom-make my online wedding invitation?",
  "response": "Creating a custom online wedding invitation can be a fun and personal way to invite your guests. Here's a step-by-step guide to help you create your invitation:\n\n### Step 1: Choose a Platform or Tool\nThere are many online tools and platforms designed for creating digital invitations. Some popular options include:\n- **Canva**: Offers customizable templates and a user-friendly interface.\n- **Evite**: Specializes in online invitations and event management.\n- **Paperless Post**: Provides elegant designs and tracking features.\n- **Minted**: Known for its high-quality and unique designs.\n- **Adobe Spark**: Allows for detailed customization and creative designs.\n\n### Step 2: Select a Template or Start from Scratch\nOnce you've chosen a platform, you can either:\n- **Select a Template**: Browse through available templates suited for wedding invitations, then customize it to fit your needs.\n- **Start from Scratch**: If you prefer, start with a blank canvas and design every element according to your vision.\n\n### Step 3: Customize Your Invitation\n#### Design Elements\n- **Color Scheme**: Choose colors that match your wedding theme.\n- **Fonts**: Select fonts that reflect the tone of your wedding (elegant, modern, rustic, etc.).\n- **Images**: Add high-quality images related to your wedding theme. This could include photos of the couple, venue, etc.\n- **Icons and Graphics**: Incorporate decorative elements like flowers, hearts, rings, etc.\n\n#### Information\n- **Wedding Date and Time**: Clearly state the date and time.\n- **Venue**: Provide the location with address details.\n- **Dress Code**: Mention if there's a specific dress code.\n- **RSVP**: Include an RSVP section with an email or link to manage responses.\n- **Additional Details**: Mention any other important information such as parking, accommodations, or special instructions.\n\n### Step 4: Add Personal Touches\n- **Quotes or Sayings**: Include a meaningful quote or poem.\n- **Personal Message**: Write a personal message to your guests.\n- **Monogram**: Add a custom monogram or logo that represents the couple.\n\n### Step 5: Review and Finalize\n- **Proofread**: Check for any spelling errors or incorrect information.\n- **Preview**: Ensure the design looks good on various devices (desktop, mobile, tablet).\n- **Feedback**: Optionally, you can get feedback from friends or family before finalizing.\n\n### Step 6: Send Your Invitation\n- **Email**: Send the invitation via email, ensuring all email addresses are correctly entered.\n- **Online Platforms**: Use platforms like Evite or Paperless Post to track RSVPs and manage guest lists.\n- **Social Media**: Share the invitation through private messages or posts if appropriate.\n\nBy following these steps, you can create a beautiful and personalized online wedding invitation that will delight your guests and help set the tone for your special day.",
